{
  "texts": [
    "This approach recognizes that while academic scores are important, they should not be the only measure of student ability.",
    "The practice of the reform includes practical courses, activities, and project-based learning to cultivate students' abilities in problem solving, communication, teamwork and critical thinking, which are critical for students to overcome the challenges of academic and professional life.",
    "In addition, students gain a sense of accomplishment in learning through interesting activities, forming a positive learning attitude and a lifelong passion for acquiring knowledge.",
    "Equity and access to quality education are key considerations in this reform.",
    "Given the uneven distribution of educational resources across schools, implementation of these reforms should be gradual."
  ]
}